Renting an apartment in Cairo, Egypt, involves several steps, legal requirements, and potential scams to be aware of. Here's a comprehensive guide based on the most recent information:

**1. Finding an Apartment:**

*   **Online Platforms:** Explore online platforms like Airbnb, which offers short and long-term rentals in major Egyptian cities [egyptadventurestravel](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-0).
*   **Real Estate Agents:** Engage a real estate agent or property management company. They can provide listings matching your preferences, negotiate leases, handle paperwork, and ensure the property meets legal requirements [housesolutionegypt](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-1) [housesolutionegypt](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-2). Verify the agent's license with the Egyptian Real Estate Association [housepointegypt](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3).
*   **Social Media:** Utilize Facebook groups where landlords advertise apartments and renters post accommodation requests [egyptadventurestravel](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-0).
*   **Word of Mouth:** Seek recommendations from friends or contacts who have rented similar properties [expat](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-4).

**2. Legal and Documentation Requirements:**

*   **Lease Agreement:** A written lease agreement is crucial. It should be in duplicate, with a copy for both parties, and signed by a witness [expat](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-4). Key elements include the rent amount, payment due dates, security deposit requirements, lease term length, house rules, utilities covered, notice period for moving out, and maintenance responsibilities [housesolutionegypt](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-1).
*   **Landlord Registration:** Landlords must register their property with the government, and tenants may need to register with the police within a week of moving in [housesolutionegypt](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-1).
*   **Passport Copy:** Landlords often require a copy of your passport [reddit](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-5) [egyptadventurestravel](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-0). You also have the right to ask for a copy of the landlord's ID [reddit](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-5).

**3. Lease Agreement Essentials:**

*   **Lease Duration:** Lease agreements typically range from one to three years, with shorter terms available [housepointegypt](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3). Specify the exact duration in the contract [housepointegypt](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3).
*   **Rent Increase:** Expect annual rent increases. A common increase is around 10% [housepointegypt](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3).
*   **Responsibilities and Bills:** Clearly define responsibilities for utilities (electricity, water, gas, internet) and repairs (major repairs by landlords, minor fixes by tenants) in the agreement [housepointegypt](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3).
*   **Early Termination:** Discuss and document conditions for early lease termination [housepointegypt](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3).
*   **Renewal Options:** Include potential renewal terms [housepointegypt](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3).

**4. Financial Aspects:**

*   **Finder's Fee:** If a third party assists in finding the property, a finder's fee (often one month's rent) may be payable [housepointegypt](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3).
*   **Deposit:** Expect to pay a deposit, typically three to four months' rent [housepointegypt](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3). Landlords often try to keep the deposit, so notify them a month before leaving and use the deposit for the last month's rent [reddit](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-5).
*   **Rent Payment:** Landlords may prefer advance payments (quarterly, half-yearly, or yearly), potentially leading to a better price [housesolutionegypt](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-2).
*   **Property Tax:** A 10% tax on the property's annual rental value may apply, with exemptions for properties valued under 500,000 LE [housepointegypt](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3).

**5. Property Inspection and Condition:**

*   **Pre-Rental Inspection:** Inspect the property thoroughly before signing the contract, documenting any existing damage in the lease agreement [consortiolawfirm](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-6) [expat](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-4).
*   **Photographic Evidence:** Take photos of the apartment's condition upon moving in to avoid disputes later [reddit](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-5).
*   **Utilities:** Ask for proof that all utility accounts are paid up before moving in [reddit](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-5).

**6. Potential Scams and How to Avoid Them:**

*   **Unbelievably Low Prices:** Be wary of properties offered at significantly low prices, as this is a common scam tactic [housesolutionegypt](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-7).
*   **Fake Websites/Listings:** Scammers use fake websites with attractive properties and fabricated testimonials [housesolutionegypt](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-7). Conduct thorough research before engaging with any online platform [housesolutionegypt](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-7).
*   **Verify Legitimacy:** Verify the real estate company's legitimacy by visiting their physical location [housesolutionegypt](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-7).
*   **"Landlord" Imposters:** Some individuals may falsely claim to be the landlord. Request to see proof of ownership [reddit](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-5).
*   **Unreturned Deposits:** Landlords may try to keep the deposit [reddit](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-5).
*   **Key to apartment:** Change the locks after moving in to ensure only you have access [reddit](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-5).

**7. Recent Legislative Changes (2025):**

*   **Old Rent Law Amendments:** Egypt's Parliament has approved amendments to the Old Rent Law, introducing a transitional framework for phasing out long-term rental contracts under the old rent system [cairoscene](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-8).
*   **Transitional Period:** Tenants of residential units have a seven-year transitional period before they must vacate the property [cairoscene](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-8) [egyptianstreets](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-9). For commercial and administrative properties, the period is five years [cairoscene](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-8).
*   **Rent Increases:** The law introduces significant increases in legal rental value, with annual increases of 15% during the transitional period [cairoscene](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-8) [egyptianstreets](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-9).
*   **New Rental Values:** In high-end residential areas, rent will rise significantly, with a minimum of EGP 1,000. Rent will also increase in mid-range and economic areas [cairoscene](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-8) [egyptianstreets](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-9).
*   **Alternative Housing:** The government is proposing alternative housing options for tenants whose contracts expire, including subsidized rent, rent-to-own schemes, and apartments available through real estate financing [egyptindependent](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-10).

**8. General Advice:**

*   **Seek Legal Advice:** Consult a lawyer to review the lease and provide legal advice [housepointegypt](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3) [housesolutionegypt](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-1).
